  "title": "Soundness of First-Order Logic",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "The standard inference rules for first-order logic (UI, UG, EI, EG, and the\npropositional rules) are sound: they preserve truth in all structures.\n\nIf $\\Gamma \\vdash \\varphi$, then $\\Gamma \\models \\varphi$.",
